com.github.fge.lambdas

Class Throwing

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.fge.lambdas.Throwing

  • public class Throwing
extends Object
    Class to invoke throwing instance chains

    You may instantiate this class if you wish, for instance, to add your own throwing instances of existing functional interfaces (either your own, or those of the JDK not covered by this package).

    All method names are defined after the non throwing instance they provide a chain for (for instance, Throwing.function(), Throwing.consumer(), etc etc).

    See Also:
